description:
## Problem
`tests/tenant/test_repository_parity.py::TestRepositoryParityGate::test_every_method_covered_or_opted_out` fails because `COVERED_METHODS` is missing 47 method names introduced across recent commits. The ORM tenant filter covers them all (they take `WorkspaceContext` and filter by `workspace_id` per the existing `TestScopedRowIsolation` proof), so the right action is to add them to `COVERED_METHODS`, not opt them out.

Methods missing (one-line summary):
- app.domain.expenses.approval.{approve_claim, list_pending, mark_reimbursed, reject_claim}
- app.domain.expenses.claims.{attach_receipt, cancel_claim, create_claim, detach_receipt, get_claim, list_for_user, list_for_workspace, submit_claim, update_claim}
- app.domain.identity.user_work_roles.{create, delete, get, list, update}_user_work_role
- app.domain.identity.work_engagements.{archive, get, list, reinstate, update}_work_engagement
- app.domain.identity.work_roles.{create, get, list, update}_work_role
- app.domain.messaging.push_tokens.{get_vapid_public_key, list_for_user, register, unregister}
- app.domain.stays.ical_service.{delete_feed, disable_feed, get_plaintext_url, list_feeds, probe_feed, register_feed, update_feed}
- app.domain.tasks.comments.{delete_comment, edit_comment, get_comment, list_comments, post_comment}
- app.domain.tasks.completion.{add_note_evidence, list_evidence}
- app.domain.tasks.oneoff.{read_task, update_task}

## Fix
Add each fully-qualified name to `COVERED_METHODS` in `tests/tenant/test_repository_parity.py`, alphabetically grouped by module. Each new entry inherits the same rationale already in the file: the ORM tenant filter covers SELECT / UPDATE / DELETE through the workspace-scoped models.

## Acceptance
- [ ] `tests/tenant/test_repository_parity.py` passes.
- [ ] No new `REPOSITORY_METHOD_OPTOUTS` entries (the methods are NOT cross-workspace by design — they're standard tenant-scoped CRUD).

## Test plan
`uv run pytest tests/tenant/test_repository_parity.py -x -q`
`uv run pytest -x -q` (full suite to surface next failure if any)
